    <bioghist id="ref1" encodinganalog="description">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Lutheran Danish immigrant to the U.S. who settled at first in Carbon, Wyoming and later became a rancher in Centennial Valley, Wyoming and Ogden, Utah.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent id="ref2" encodinganalog="description">
      <p>One handwritten bound journal in Danish. Christensen talks about his voyage from Denmark to America in 1871. Daily entries begin in May 1873 and record weather conditions and mining activities in Carbon, Wyoming.</p>
    </scopecontent>
